    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 20th level, you gain the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/rules-for-monsters/creature-types#TOC-Shapechanger\">shapechanger</a>&nbsp;subtype, and you can assume the form of a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/rules-for-monsters/creature-types#TOC-Reptilian\">reptilian</a>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/rules-for-monsters/creature-types#TOC-Humanoid\">humanoid</a>&nbsp;(as @Compendium[pf1.spells.kouqz0pm1xl8xilm]{Alter Self}&nbsp;) or snake of Diminutive to Huge size (as @Compendium[pf1.spells.w88ddxpu89qcr5c0]{Beast Shape III}) at will. You retain the power of speech and the ability to use somatic spell&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Components\">components</a>&nbsp;when transformed. You also become immune to poison and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/special-abilities#TOC-Paralysis\">paralysis</a>. You may use serpentâ€™s fang as often as desired, and you may choose to inflict damage to any ability score.</p>",
